description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic nurse to join our Community Hospital Multi Disciplinary Team on Ward 1 Berwick Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time for the staff at Berwick Infirmary as we prepare for our new hospital build and as part of the nursing team you would be involved in this process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a 24 bedded Consultant lead rehabilitation ward, with daily clinical support from our local GP Practice. We support medical patients with on going rehabilitation needs following an acute illness i.e. stroke, recent surgery and those who may have some mental health needs i.e delirium / dementia. We support palliative care pathways &amp; patients admitted under the nurse to nurse pathway. We have a strong working relationship with all members of the multi disciplinary team as part of our discharge planning process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunities for extended staff development with this role. If you would like to be more autonomous in your practice while supporting the needs of the local community in a changing NHS why not join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rotational post and the successful candidates will be expected to work Night Duty as part of the role. Although this is a 30 hour post, full time hours would be considered. The successful post holder must be able to role model compassionate and inclusive leadership in order to shape the creation of a collective leadership culture within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Northumbria Healthcare Trust has just been awarded Outstanding by the CQC for the second time, come and join us and be part of the Northumbria Way..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1st Level live NMC registered Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Mentor. Mentorship qualification or relevant qualification (essential requirement for post, expectation this will be completed within an 18 month period&lt;strong&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough understanding of contemporary nursing issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the delivery of ‘Compassion in Practice’- Nursing, Midwifery and&lt;br /&gt;Care Staff Vision and Strategy incorporating the 6C’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Criteria: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PP126/7&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;D32/33&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post Registration qualification in specialty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma/degree in nursing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Gibson, ward manager, sue.gibson3@nhct.nhs.uk, 01289 356648&lt;/p&gt;
